HEADWORD: alcoholism
<hw>al"co*hol*ism</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧l"k⟦osl⟧*h⟦ocr⟧l*⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>alcoolisme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Chronic excessive drinking of alcoholic beverages
that leads to social, occupational, psychological and physiological
problems.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>AS</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Psychological and physiological
dependence on alcohol; sudden cessation of drinking may lead to
withdrawal symptoms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>AS</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alcoholization</ent>⟦br⟧
